[5] South Dakota
Date: Fri 4 Jul 2014
Source: Rapid City Journal [edited]
http://rapidcityjournal.com/news/local/lawrence-county-leads-state-with-pertussis-cases/article_74ac0968-4283-530a-9441-a8cd4149d274.html


The South Dakota Department of Health has confirmed 51 pertussis cases statewide in 2014. The majority are in Lawrence County, which has 17 confirmed cases. Ziebach County has 4 confirmed cases. Pennington, Custer, Butte, and Shannon counties have 3 or fewer cases.

3/4ths of confirmed cases are children under 15, 1/4th of whom were not vaccinated, according to State Epidemiologist Lon Kightlinger.

The Department of Health is urging those who still need to be vaccinated to contact local health providers.

